storyInfo: Snowsant finds out from Closure that the very first paper she has written in her life was submitted to the editorial board of a scientific journal. But before she even has a chance to await the results, she is struck by news that knocks the wind out of her.

attributes.content: Really? It's already been sent?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Mmhm. Handed a printed copy to the Messenger just this morning, and he took off with it right away. Now it's all up to the reviewers' feedback whether the journal picks it up.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Thank you so much, Closure — I mean, Advisor!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Oh jeez, don't call me that. I'm nowhere near qualified to give you advice in your own field. The best I could do was help you sort through your ideas.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Umm...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But you're the one who gave me the idea of writing this paper in the first place!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Sure, but I just figured it'd be a waste letting a gem like you go undiscovered.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: You also steered me in the right direction while I was writing it!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I mean, yeah, it's the first academic paper you've ever written. Of course you'd need some pointers.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: You even helped me put the finishing touches on it last night!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Snowsant, when you put it that way, I—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Yawns)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: —Don't feel so sleepy anymore.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Huh...?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I know you're a self-taught prodigy and all, and that you've always buried yourself in your research without paying much attention to academic journals and stuff...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: But putting me down as the lead author? Really? Was that like a trap so you could say I plagiarized you?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I-I didn't think the order of the authors mattered. So, as a way of showing my gratitude, I—
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'm the corresponding author, thank you very much! My name goes after!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: *sniffles*...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: And let's not even get into all the punctuation errors, mixed up heading levels, poorly marked citations, just dumping all the references at the end...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: If it's gonna be like this next time, I'll have to start charging an editing fee! One thousand LMD per word!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I'm sorry!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Lastly, can you tell why, just why, you sent it to me...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Lets out a pained yawn)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: ...Handwritten?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: No one even accepts handwritten manuscripts these days! I spent half the night just typing it all out so I could proofread it, and the other half trying to squeeze in all those charts and diagrams somehow!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: But I calculated the price of paper and ink, and found that printing it would be two LMD more expensive than writing it by hand...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Clutches her head with both hands)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Snowsant, correct me if I'm wrong, but you wanna be a great scientist, right?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: And to be a great scientist, you have to publish a lot of papers, right?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Mhm. That's what you told me.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: And do you realize that there are expenses other than paper and ink?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Such as?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Publication fees.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Publication fees? H-How much?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Depends on the journal, but it's always at least four figures.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: F-F-F-F-Four figures???
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: L-L-L-Let me figure out what expenses I can cut...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Takes out her tablet)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (First, I can't touch the money that's supposed to be sent home...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Then, there are the self-research topics... Right now, there are three items...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Lets out a long yawn)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I wouldn't worry about it too much—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (No, I can't move around the funds I've already allocated for the projects either...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Snowsant?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (The only area I can afford to cut is food expenses... Waah...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Are you listening?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Fine, whatever.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: If you're gonna be like this, I'm gonna catch me some shut-eye. I've got a meeting with Kal'tsit in ten minutes.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Closure casually grabs a nearby book and drapes it over her face before slumping back into her chair and letting out even, rhythmic snores.
(I don't know even know when this fee is due... But if I can have it pushed back, maybe I can scrounge up enough money...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Um, C-Closure...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: She's asleep?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Snowsant?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Is Closure asleep?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Um, yes... It's all my fault...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I don't think you did anything wrong.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Things never go right the first time. As long as you apologize and don't make the same mistakes next time, it'll be fine. That's what Liskarm always tells me, anyway.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Mm... Thank you...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Sorry for bringing you all the way to the cafeteria just to drink plain water with me.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Don't worry about it.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: So, were you looking for Closure for something?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: There's something wrong with my communications terminal, but Engineering's had its hands full of late. If I went through the standard channels, it'd take three whole months to get it fixed.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Yesterday I finally mustered the courage to head to Lutra to ask Mayer for help, but she's also really busy...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: So I made up my mind to report the problem to Closure directly... but she was asleep.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Is it serious?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Well, it's not like it's unusable. The main issue is that the signal gets choppy sometimes, but Engineering's been pushing it back because it's low priority.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Have you tried taking it apart? If it's a bad connection or something along those lines, maybe you could fix it yourself.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'm afraid of breaking the parts inside...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Um, maybe I can give it a try?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Really? You'd do that for me?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: If it's not something I can handle on my own, I'll just put it back together, so don't worry.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: You fixed it already?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: There was a small metal component in its Originium circuitry that rusted, so I replaced it. You shouldn't have any more issues with choppiness.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Here you go!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Woah... Let me give it a try.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Umm...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Is something wrong?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I want to test it, but I'm not sure who to call... I wouldn't want to bother anyone.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Why not just... pick one at random?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I-I'll figure something out.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Umm... Is this Liskarm?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Yes... My terminal's been fixed...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: It's not cutting out at all... or making any static...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Oh right, now I won't have to guess whether Franka's being serious or just joking around...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Sounds good!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Mmhmm! Bye!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Thanks again, Snowsant. How much do I owe you?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Huh? Umm...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Let's not worry about that... It was just a tiny metal part, and I basically recycled it from the Engineering Department. It's not like I had to buy it or anything...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Materials are one thing, but your labor is another.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Just now, Liskarm mentioned that she'll go to you if she needs a terminal fixed. More people might need things fixed too, so we can't have you going into the red for them.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: I think you should charge something. It's only fair.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: (More people... Need things fixed... Charge something... It's only fair...)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (The publication fees!)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Th-Th-Then... I'll take you up on that!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Mhm.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: (Breathes deeply)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Then... How about twenty LMD?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Twenty?!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: But didn't you say your publication fee was in the four-digit range?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: I know it isn't much, but high volume with low margins is the best way of doing business. Nobody would come if I charged too much...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: So, twenty is enough. Twenty is just right.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Phew... That takes care of everything.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Now, to check the tags...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: These two terminals belong to Liskarm and Kroos.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: There's also Vanilla's pet water dispenser, and Instructor Dur-nar's calculator.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Including Jessica's terminal from yesterday, that makes a total of five times twenty.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: So, that's a hundred LMD in one day. Making money this way... seems pretty fast?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: A four-figure publication fee... Assuming it's just five thousand, then the amount I've earned today would be—
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: One-fiftieth...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I need to work harder.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But I wonder why all these communication terminals have the same problem?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Mine doesn't though. How strange.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Who is it? Come in.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: It's me, Jessica.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Hi there. I've finished repairing everything, so you can take them back now.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Sounds good!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: This is what we owe you. One hundred LMD.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: You're paying me now? What if there still are problems...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Instructor Dur-nar said that making you do minor repair jobs is selling your abilities short.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Oh! Um, tell her I appreciate that!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Then, er, thank you for the payment.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Oh, by the way, why do all your terminals have the same point of failure? Is there some kind of design flaw?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I asked Liskarm, and she thinks they sacrificed reliability for performance, and used relatively rust-prone materials in the circuitry...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Which I guess would be the component you mentioned.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: It wouldn't be a problem under ordinary conditions, but operators often have to work in hot or humid environments, so the terminals break down faster.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: And is there no way to make it work without that part?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I don't know... Not even Closure could do anything about it, after all.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Oh right, Instructor Dur-nar asked me to tell you one more thing.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: She said it's fine to have you work on minor stuff like water dispensers and calculators, but it's best for Engineering to handle standard-issue things like the terminals.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Why's that?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: As a policy, Engineering doesn't want us doing private maintenance on standard-issue equipment. Repairing things using inconsistent materials will just make future maintenance more expensive.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Wh-What do I do then? Should I talk to Instructor Dur-nar...?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Don't worry about it.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: She said she'd turn a blind eye to it, given your circumstances and the fact that Engineering has such a back-log these days.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: She just wanted to remind you to use your own judgment.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: (Lets out a long sigh)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: So, next time someone asks you to fix their terminal, would you still agree to it?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: That's...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I guess I'll use my own judgment.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Orchid's fountain pen, twenty LMD.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Hibiscus's food processor, twenty LMD.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: April's music player, twenty LMD—but it took two LMD to replace the buttons, and another one to replace the exposed headphone cable so she doesn't notice anything. So, that's a net of seventeen LMD.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Durin's nail clippers...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Even an amateur could reassemble a nail clipper, so I won't charge anything for that.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Altogether, that's only fifty-seven LMD this week...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: What do I do? If business continues to be this bad, I won't be able to make five thousand...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Plus, how much time do I even have to come up with the publication fee?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Snowsant lies down on the chair, involuntarily glancing at the eight terminals sitting on the table, awaiting repairs.
If I fix all of them, that'd be a hundred-sixty LMD!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: No, no. It was one thing when I didn't know about the regulations, it's another to knowingly break the rules...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But, the publication fee...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: *sob*... I don't want money to be the first stumbling block on my way to becoming a great scientist.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Hmm, what if I replace the structure of the Originium circuit entirely, and find a workaround that doesn't use metal parts at all? Would that still violate the regulations?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But how could I manage something not even Closure could?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: No, I have to give it a shot. For the publication fee.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'll repair everyone else's terminals using the old method first, then use my own to fiddle with the Originium circuitry.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: You can do it, Snowsant! You have to do it, so you can get your papers published, become a great scientist, and afford to have three meals a day... with dessert!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Work... Projects... Things to fix... Everything looks good.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: It's one o'clock, huh?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Maybe I'll stay up a bit later tonight... Need to investigate how the circuitry in the terminal is connected.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: It's only 10:30, and I'm already done with all my work. Guess I was pretty lucky today.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Now, time to take a look at that circuitry.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Can't connect it like this, or like this...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Ugh, I've already spent weeks on the circuitry alone.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But if I try using this—
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Wait, I haven't worked on today's research project yet. I've got to take care of that first.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Phew... Haah...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I have a good feeling about this one. The connection might just work.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Time to pull an all-nighter!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Huh? You want me to grab all the terminals you've already fixed? You're going to go over them all again?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: It's because I found a new way to connect the circuitry, a simpler way that bypasses the need for the metal part that rusts easily.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Not even Closure could figure it out!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Hmm, now that you mention it... I guess so?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Let me try to remember whose terminals you fixed...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: I've kept the receipts, so we can go off of that.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Me, Liskarm, Kroos...
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Oh right, considering this is an upgrade, you can't just charge the same twenty LMD, right?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: True. Since I decided to make this change on my own, I can't ask for your money at all.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: ...Huh?
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Well, aren't you just a saint, Snowsant?
Heheh...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: That's right! She's been hard at work fixing up the terminals for how many days now? How can she not charge a cent for them—
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: C-C-Closure?!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Wow, I'm here for two seconds and I'm already hearing all about your under-the-table dealings.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Jessica, since you're only an accomplice, head back to the dorms for now. I need to have a word with the prime suspect first.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Y-Yes, ma'am!
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: Snowsant?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: What, so scared you can't walk?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: ...N-No, that's not it.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Then come on in and let's have a chat.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Close the door.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Yeah...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: First of all, let me ask: how are your personal projects and daily work going? How much are you letting this side gig get in the way?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I-It's not getting in the way at all! I'm finishing all my work as always, and I'm making progress in my projects too!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Really? Then when are you getting to sleep every night?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Somewhere around... three or four?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Ahem, moving on then.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Given how you're trembling like a baby fowlbeast, I take it you realize the problems this business of yours could cause.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Yeah...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Let's hear it then.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Privately repairing standard-issue equipment without authorization might increase the Engineering Department's maintenance expenses further down the road...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Mhm, sounds like you really know your stuff. Who told you that? Jessica?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Instructor Dur-nar reminded me.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Dur-nar?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Nods)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Glad to hear our old vets still have their priorities straight—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Wait, hold up, she told you all that, but didn't bother stopping you? Or even reporting it to me?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Great, sounds like I've another score to settle.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: This has nothing to do with her... It was my own decision.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Do you really have the luxury of worrying about others right now?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Engineering's already overwhelmed with all sorts of orders and requests. This terminal repair thing might be what finally breaks the burdenbeast's back. You get what I'm saying?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: All their metal components originally came from the same batch. Even if some go bad faster or slower, they fall in pretty much the same window. We're already trying to squeeze in time to put together an organized repair-and-replace.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: But now, since some of them are fixed but others aren't, that's just one more set of data points for us to wrangle.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I... I have a ledger, and I've kept track of whose terminals I've worked on...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'm aware you have the receipts.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: But can you guarantee that all the materials used in repairing them came from the same batch?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Which means that to make things more convenient going forward, we'll have to swap them all out again anyway, which is a complete waste of resources!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Sure, we're only talking a few dozen metal components this time, but who knows how big the bill will be next time!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I understand. I know I did wrong...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (I was planning on giving her a stern talking-to, but seeing how obedient she's being, it's hard to find the words...)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Ahem.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Anyway, as the head of Engineering, I'm declaring that as of today, your repair shop is closed indefinitely!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I-I accept your punishment...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: W-Waaah...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Shoot, she seriously started crying... Was I too hard on her?)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: C'mon, stop that. Stop crying.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Blows nose)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: So, why did you decide to start doing this in the first place?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I don't have any money, so I can't afford the publication fee...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Publication fee?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Wait, didn't I already tell you—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Oh, I guess I forgot, huh?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Wait, this might be a bitter pill to swallow, but she needs to learn her lesson. Can't let it become water under the bridge that easily.)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: In any case, don't do it again.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Let me take a look at your ledger and see how much money you made.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: ...Your net profit was only a thousand LMD?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: And you even covered the cost of materials beyond the scope of the request, out-of-pocket?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: AND you waived the entire bill for someone?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: In the end, you fixed up over a hundred items and only made a thousand LMD?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I was aiming for high volume through low prices, so I set the price at twenty LMD...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: There's a floor to how low you can go with that strategy!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I got a mean fifty LMD just from changing out the power cord of the Doctor's kettle while they were busy going through paperwork!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: A power cord doesn't cost that much, does it? Plus, you're basically just plugging it in, aren't you?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Ah, ahem. That was simply an example.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Fifty LMD might be a bit overkill for a hot water kettle, but we're talking high-tech terminals here!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Repairing delicate machinery like that means taking them apart with specialized tools and carefully replacing the components. That's gotta be worth at least fifty or sixty!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: But back on topic—your paper has basically already been accepted. It only needs some minor tweaks and it's ready to publish.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I was only stopping by to hand you the reviewer's comments when I caught you running a black market repair shop in the dorm hallway.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Wait... What did you just say? My paper... It only needs a few minor revisions?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: This isn't a dream, is it?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: What do you think?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Also, I have another piece of good news—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Whispers) I should've told you this first, but better late than never.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: You don't have to pay the publication fee either.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Wh-Wh-Wh-What?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'm your corresponding author, and Rhodes Island is your employer. Naturally, we'll be covering the fee, so you can stop worrying about breaking the bank.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Really?!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I can't believe this, I need to pinch myself—
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Ow!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Oh my gosh!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Ohmygosh, Closure! I'm going to be published!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Waaaah, I'm finally going to be published! My paper is going to be...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Have you calmed down yet?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Rubs eyes)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Mmhmm!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: The publication fee was originally two grand, but I applied for a special hardship grant for you, and managed to get it down to fifteen hundred.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Rhodes Island can easily cover that, so you don't need to stay up all night fixing toasters anymore.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: That's...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I just realized that, in the end, you're just paying it for me...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Yeah, so?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Um... Isn't that a bit...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: A bit what?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I-I'm thinking that maybe...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Maybe, the publication fee... I...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I think... I should pay it myself after all.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: You and Rhodes Island have been so good to me, but all I've done is give you more work. I'd feel bad taking your money too...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I respect the hustle, but you're still short five hundo.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I can, um, make up the difference by continuing to fix things for people...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Huuuh?!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Not the standard-issue equipment, I promise! I'll stick to fountain pens and water dispensers, I swear!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: I'm sorry, I'm sorry! I know you already let me off easy, and I feel really bad about it!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But if I accept someone else's charity and use their money to pay the fee without earning it myself, I won't be able to sleep at night!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Snowsant, are you serious?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: (Breathes deeply)
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Yes, I'm dead serious.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Can you guarantee it won't get in the way of your work or your research?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I swear it!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: You might not even get any business without these terminals, you know.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I will.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: You sure?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I-I can go around asking everyone if they need anything fixed. I'm sure there'll be someone!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: (Chuckles wryly)
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Well, knock yourself out.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Does that mean... I can continue fixing things for people?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: What, are you trying to get me to change my mind now?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: N-N-No! Thank you so much, Closure!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: But remember to raise your prices. Twenty is lowballing it so much I feel secondhand pain.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I will!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Also, you'd better get your butt in bed by midnight every night.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: That... might be asking a bit much...
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: It's not up for negotiation. If anyone else gets sick, I'll give them sick leave; but if you get sick... I'm cutting your wages!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Noooo! Fine, I understand!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: One last thing. I overheard you and Jessica talking about how you managed to simplify the design and bypass the metal component?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: Do you have a blueprint? Let me take a look.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Mhm...
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Well, I'll be. That's just crazy enough to work.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Snowsant, I'm going to take this with me and look into it a bit more, maybe make a few improvements. If all goes well, you'll be in charge of rolling out the standardized updates for all our terminals.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Huh? You're... putting me in charge?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: It's your blueprint, your idea, your hours of lost sleep. Who else would be in charge?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Also, this approach is pretty novel. After you make some progress with your work, keep looking into it. Who knows, maybe you've already got a second paper on your hands?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: A-A-A second paper?!
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: C-Closure! I-Isn't it a bit early to think about my second paper when my first still hasn't been published?
attributes.name: Snowsant

attributes.content: And what's wrong with that? If you've got the ability and the work ethic, why shouldn't your hard work be rewarded?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Alright, go celebrate with Jessica. I've still got a meeting to get to, so I can't join you.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Oh, and before I forget again, here's the letter from the reviewer!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Bye bye!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.text: The manuscript you submitted to this journal (No. 011224) has passed preliminary review, but also requires certain revisions.

The reviewer's comments are attached to this letter. Please submit the revised manuscript to the editorial board before the deadline. If you have any other questions, please feel free to contact the board. Thank you for your dedication to theoretical research!
The shortcomings of this paper are obvious.

The author is unaware of the latest breakthroughs in this field, and often runs into the problem of 'reinventing the wheel' in regards to theoretical derivations; experimental design is excessively rigid with a focus on theory over practice, ignoring the applications of new technologies in the field, etc.
However, the author's originality, sensitivity to practical issues, and meticulous thoughtfulness in laying out the argument are all admirable.
Above all, the author has overcome many of the aforementioned problems with a degree of perseverance and diligence far beyond most people, which has impressed us deeply.
We hope that the author will continue to maintain this diligence and venture ever further on the road of academia.
